reviewText: I enjoyed this movie, keeping you on the edge of your seat ... a thriller with dramatic turns. reviewText: Shannen Doherty plays Kate who is Pregnant and her boyfriend Paul played by Max Martini both have different feeling about the baby. Kate has to go think about things and when she gets back she finds that the factory that they both worked at is on fire and Paul has died. the movie then jumps to kate having her baby. Kate's best friend David played by Julian McMahon is there with support and helps kate deal with Paul's death. what Kate doesn't know is that David has been in love with her for years. One day David and Kate are out by the lake when she goes into it and she almost drowns. When she wakes on the beach she sees Paul and she freaks out because he is dead right. she relieze that she woke two days before his death and she thinks and hopes she can provent his death from ever happening. Now the question is does she change her future and saves Paul or does she let him die and be with David.

reviewText: So many twist and turns that you will be kept on your toes all the way through.  After she loses her partner in a fire she manages to survive for years with her only child.  With a helping hand and friend David starts to bring back her trust and life together as she starts to live again. One day she has a mysterious near drowning that has her dreaming of two days before her first boyfriend Paul dies,and is now at the cross roads wandering weather to trust fate and save him or continue on this path with David her new one. I rated this an A grade plus for been very different and with so many things going on that you can hardly stay up with them. Story line is fabulous and the cast are brilliant, a thriller that will hold your attention to the very end. I hope you have the popcorn ready with your feet up and relaxing in your favourite chair for a marvellous night in with a great old classic for sheer entertainment. Enjoy!

reviewText: I liked the plot description, and I like time travel, people-out-of-place stories, so I thought I would try this.  It was kind of a cross between "The Lake House" and "Premonition."  It even had Julian McMahon in it - for that alone I would watch it.  It's an enjoyable story - a little slow-paced at times, with shots of the countryside and sunshine on the river, but worth watching.
